name: Music Contest in Dieppe
obverse: A seated woman facing right. To her right are two mermaids holding mirrors. Between them is the coat of arms of Dieppe. Behind them is the city of Dieppe.
reverse: Three panels showing views of Dieppe. In the foreground is a plaque surrounded by naval instruments and sea shells.
reverse_inscriptions: LA VILLE DE DIEPPE A M. DUJARDIN BEAUMETZ CONCOURS MUSICAL 10 JUILLET 1905
description: This medal was made to commemorate a music contest held in Dieppe, France on July 10, 1905.
